2.0 Planed feature set:

- Revamped all textures!

- Merlin Vacuum foil.

- Revamped Landing Leg Meshes.

- Thicker Raceways and Integrated RCS.

- Support for Launchers Pack AND Tundra Exploration!

- Revamped Fairing textures.

- Revamped Interstage.

- Animated Falcon Heavy booster struts.

- Animated interstage hydraulic pusher.

- One part, thrust configurable engine block.

- Entirely independent, relying modifications through MM scripts.

HELP WANTED!!!

If you have any experience with KSP modding,

particularly animations, meshes, and unity integration 

please let me know! (DM or Discord (Space Bird#4609)) 

Your help will be much appreciated to make this

mod the highest quality it can possibly be!

Hey, thanks for your work @SpaceBirb!

I've just updated the SpaceX Pack to work with KSP 1.4.2 and thus, I also removed firespitter as a dependency because now in 1.4, the module "ModulePartVariants" lets you apply different textures to one part, go check out some squad configs for fuel tanks or the new parts from the expansion to see how that works.

It would be great if you could drop the firespitter dependency as well and also switch to the stock module, otherwise users will need to install firespitter for this expansion to work.

Also, would it be possible to not replace the original configs, but rather make a module manager patch for the changed parts? I am not too familiar with MM but I think there's gotta be a feature which simply lets you "add" some stuff to an already existing line, you might need to ask someone else or look in the documentation, but that would be great so custom textures  won't need to be inserted into the cfg again.

If you have questions how the new stock module works, feel free to ask and I'll help you! (also I've changed some names so be careful when applying your textures!)

Thanks,

KK

I have a question: How does this not overwrite the original textures given that the files you say to replace the original ones with are smaller (and therefore can't have all the data in the old textures)?

On ‎6‎/‎24‎/‎2018 at 4:50 PM, IMLL1 said:

I have a question: How does this not overwrite the original textures given that the files you say to replace the original ones with are smaller (and therefore can't have all the data in the old textures)?

It may be because of the B5 texture format mainly being formatted in .png, and .dds. Instead of the regular textures being formatted in mainly .dds. Adding png's may compress the file size a bit. Other than that, I'm not too sure. As for the configuration files, they are the same format, and therefore larger. But the size of the textures is smaller because of different formats.

Hi SpaceBird :) i don't understand, i'm putting the extracted files into game data/launcher packs/rockets/spaceX/ and it wont change anything, i still have the white block 4 falcon 9, any ideas on how to fix it ?

On 8/6/2018 at 3:38 PM, RandomDude said:

Hi SpaceBird i don't understand, i'm putting the extracted files into game data/launcher packs/rockets/spaceX/ and it wont change anything, i still have the white block 4 falcon 9, any ideas on how to fix it ?

Hello! 



You may be doing a couple of things wrong, installed the wrong version, forgetting a dependency, etc.

First off, if you have KSP 1.4 and up, (1.4,1.4.1,2,3 etc.) you'll need to download B5 V1.3. If you're running KSP 1.3.1 or lower, you'll have to download B5 V1.2, and use firespitter for texture changes.

If you have installed it correctly, you'll have to right click the part that you want to change textures in order to display the texture-changing menu.

If you still have trouble, please let me know!
